Parliament, Monday, 20 August 2018 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will tomorrow hold a hearing with the Department of Public Works on irregular, fruitless and wasteful expenditure. Details of the hearing: Date: Tuesday, 21 August 2018 Time: 09:00 Venue: V454, Old Assembly Building, Parliament ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF SCOPA, MR THEMBA GODI. For media enquiries, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
